# Slidesmith is bring-your-own-keys. The easiest way to configure it is the
# in-app Settings screen — keys are saved to ~/.slidesmith/config.json.
#
# These env vars are optional overrides for self-hosting / headless setups:

# Port the local Slidesmith server listens on (default 8787).
# PORT=8787

# Interface to bind (default 127.0.0.1 — loopback only). The server returns
# your API keys to the Settings UI, so DO NOT expose it to a network unless
# you're behind a firewall and know what you're doing.
# HOST=127.0.0.1

# Where config + the generation queue are stored (default ~/.slidesmith).
# SLIDESMITH_DIR=/path/to/data

# You do NOT need to put API keys here — enter them in Settings instead.
# (post-bridge key for scheduling/posting/analytics, OpenRouter key for the AI.)
